+# Chroma Multi-Crate Workspace
+
+This is a multi-crate workspace for the Chroma project, designed to improve modularity and enable benchmarking.
+
+## Crates
+
+### `chroma-core`
+Contains core functionality shared between services:
+- Assignment management
+- Blockstore operations
+- Caching mechanisms
+- Compaction logic
+- Configuration handling
+- Distance metrics
+- Execution engines
+- Indexing systems
+- Logging utilities
+- Memberlist management
+- Segment handling
+- Storage systems
+- System components
+- Tracing capabilities
+- Type definitions
+- Utility functions
+
+### `chroma-api`
+Contains API definitions and service interfaces for communication between components.
+
+### `worker`
+Main service binaries:
+- Query service
+- Compaction service
+
+### `chroma-benchmarks`
+Contains benchmark implementations for performance testing and measurement.
+
+## Building and Testing
+
+To build all crates:
 ```bash
-pip install chromadb # python client
-# for javascript, npm install chromadb!
-# for client-server mode, chroma run --path /chroma_db_path
+cargo build
 ```
 
-The core API is only 4 functions (run our [💡 Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1QEzFyqnoFxq7LUGyP1vzR4iLt9PpCDXv?usp=sharing) or [Replit template](https://replit.com/@swyx/BasicChromaStarter?v=1)):
-
-```python
-import chromadb
-# setup Chroma in-memory, for easy prototyping. Can add persistence easily!
-client = chromadb.Client()
-
-# Create collection. get_collection, get_or_create_collection, delete_collection also available!
-collection = client.create_collection("all-my-documents")
-
-# Add docs to the collection. Can also update and delete. Row-based API coming soon!
-collection.add(
-    documents=["This is document1", "This is document2"], # we handle tokenization, embedding, and indexing automatically. You can skip that and add your own embeddings as well
-    metadatas=[{"source": "notion"}, {"source": "google-docs"}], # filter on these!
-    ids=["doc1", "doc2"], # unique for each doc
-)
-
-# Query/search 2 most similar results. You can also .get by id
-results = collection.query(
-    query_texts=["This is a query document"],
-    n_results=2,
-    # where={"metadata_field": "is_equal_to_this"}, # optional filter
-    # where_document={"$contains":"search_string"}  # optional filter
-)
